WEBVTT

00:26.591 --> 00:29.029
[jazz music]

00:35.078 --> 00:38.125
[singing in Spanish]

02:09.738 --> 02:12.741
[Manuel applauding]

02:13.872 --> 02:15.961
Please, come join me.

02:16.005 --> 02:16.832
Please, come.

02:20.879 --> 02:22.664
[Manuel speaking Spanish]

02:22.707 --> 02:23.491
Gracias.

02:30.019 --> 02:33.849
- Bravissima. I'm a big fan of
your voice.

02:33.892 --> 02:36.199
You have an exceptional talent.

02:36.243 --> 02:37.896
Thank you [chuckles].

02:37.940 --> 02:40.029
- Apologies. Where are my
manners?

02:40.072 --> 02:41.857
What can I get you to drink?

02:41.900 --> 02:44.033
Oh, I'm okay, thank you.

02:44.076 --> 02:46.166
- Please, after a performance
like that,

02:46.209 --> 02:49.473
you certainly earned one, for
sure.

02:49.517 --> 02:50.300
Yes?

02:51.693 --> 02:54.522
- Okay, I'll have a
glass of red wine please.

02:54.565 --> 02:57.699
- Akheem, bring me one bottle
of this new French red wine

02:57.742 --> 02:58.917
we just received yesterday.

02:58.961 --> 02:59.788
Yes, sir.

03:02.747 --> 03:04.880
You're from Chicago, right?

03:04.923 --> 03:07.056
You must be fan of cold winters
then?

03:07.099 --> 03:10.538
- Oh no, I hate the cold
actually.

03:10.581 --> 03:14.629
I'm from Florida, but I moved
away as soon as I could.

03:14.672 --> 03:16.108
To chase a dream.

03:16.152 --> 03:18.023
And cold winters just became a
price

03:18.067 --> 03:19.242
for that dream, I guess.

03:20.200 --> 03:22.071
It's paradise here.

03:22.114 --> 03:25.074
Rarely gets below 72 degrees.

03:27.555 --> 03:31.298
I'm offering you three times
whatever you make in Chicago

03:31.341 --> 03:34.823
to sing here in my club,
exclusively for me.

03:37.042 --> 03:39.567
- My God, that's an amazing
offer.

03:40.916 --> 03:43.135
[wine pouring]

03:43.179 --> 03:44.093
- I'm so sorry, ma'am. Let me
get that.

03:44.136 --> 03:45.660
- It's all right.
- I'm so sorry.

03:45.703 --> 03:47.183
It's not your fault.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.925
Akheem, it's okay, calm down.

03:49.968 --> 03:53.276
She's right. It certainly was an
accident.

03:53.320 --> 03:55.278
How long have you been
working for me, Akheem?

03:56.714 --> 03:58.194
Almost two months, sir.

03:58.238 --> 04:00.805
- Then you know the customer is
king.

04:00.849 --> 04:04.896
The customer deserve
excellent service, always.

04:04.940 --> 04:06.724
Yes, sir. I'm so sorry, sir.

04:06.768 --> 04:07.551
I'm sorry, ma'am.

04:07.595 --> 04:08.639
It's okay.

04:08.683 --> 04:09.466
I'm so so sorry.

04:09.510 --> 04:11.947
[blood flowing]

04:11.990 --> 04:13.557
You should be sorry.

04:13.601 --> 04:16.255
[blood flowing]

04:16.298 --> 04:18.910
[Akheem gasping]

04:18.954 --> 04:22.130
[soft dramatic music]

04:31.662 --> 04:32.489
Apologies.

04:34.317 --> 04:37.755
Why you don't go to get
cleaned up a little bit?

04:37.799 --> 04:40.367
Then come sing for me something
special.

04:40.410 --> 04:43.544
[soft dramatic music]

04:48.766 --> 04:51.726
You work for me now.

04:51.769 --> 04:53.858
[Nora whimpering]

04:53.902 --> 04:57.732
[soft dramatic music]

04:57.775 --> 04:59.908
[waves lapping]

04:59.951 --> 05:03.128
[soft dramatic music]

05:11.311 --> 05:14.009
[dramatic music]

05:18.056 --> 05:21.016
[soft dramatic music]

05:34.203 --> 05:36.858
- So, I finally had to
tell her last night.

05:36.901 --> 05:38.163
Bon voyage, Coco.

05:41.166 --> 05:42.429
You know, I know she was
wrong for me from the moment

05:42.472 --> 05:45.127
we met, but was she beautiful,
man.

05:45.170 --> 05:47.347
She had them long legs she
would just wrap around me.

05:47.390 --> 05:50.959
Crystal blue eyes, like
swimming pools of beauty.

05:51.002 --> 05:52.003
Just, mm [inhales].

05:54.789 --> 05:56.921
Hey, Mark, I'm over here just
pouring my heart out to you

05:56.965 --> 05:57.966
and I feel like you're not even
listening.

05:58.009 --> 05:59.010
Are you listening?

05:59.054 --> 05:59.881
No.

06:00.925 --> 06:03.101
Okay, all right. You're right.

06:03.145 --> 06:05.669
You were right, because I know,
from the moment you met her

06:05.713 --> 06:06.757
you were all like ...

06:06.801 --> 06:08.455
She wasn't right for you.

06:08.498 --> 06:10.065
And why is that, exactly?

06:11.849 --> 06:13.503
She was normal.

06:13.547 --> 06:14.112
Well, yeah.

06:15.505 --> 06:18.465
Well you know this is all
kinda your fault, right?

06:18.508 --> 06:19.030
My fault?

06:20.423 --> 06:22.251
Well yeah.

06:22.294 --> 06:24.645
We been working together
for years now, man.

06:24.688 --> 06:26.908
All you gotta do is come out
with me every once in a while,

06:26.951 --> 06:28.213
just have a couple drinks,
and maybe you could

06:28.257 --> 06:29.954
steer me clear of the wrong
girls.

06:29.998 --> 06:33.697
- I told you, I'm not into
that singles dating thing.

06:33.741 --> 06:35.786
- Singles dating scene, man,
that's all the dating scene is

06:35.830 --> 06:37.092
is a bunch of singles.

06:37.135 --> 06:39.224
Come on, man, you're the
only guy I know who's got

06:39.268 --> 06:41.052
his ex-wife's name tattooed on
his finger.

06:43.446 --> 06:47.450
- She wasn't my ex-wife
when I got the tattoo.

06:47.494 --> 06:50.148
- Yeah, I know that. Just
add a little something to it.

06:50.192 --> 06:52.237
What does that say anyway,
Attila?

06:52.281 --> 06:53.238
It's Akilah. Akilah.

06:54.979 --> 06:57.939
- Okay, so add a T and now it's
Tequila.

06:57.982 --> 06:59.244
Right? You'd be the cool guy at
the bar.

06:59.288 --> 07:00.637
You got Tequila on your knuckle.

07:00.681 --> 07:01.246
They're here.

07:02.726 --> 07:03.814
Get serious.

07:03.858 --> 07:07.252
[soft suspenseful music]

07:10.995 --> 07:12.214
Rock, paper, scissors? Hm?

07:14.956 --> 07:17.175
Okay. You always do rock anyway.

07:17.219 --> 07:20.091
[soft suspenseful music]

07:20.135 --> 07:20.962
S'up, Los.

07:22.093 --> 07:24.182
- Hello, my friend. How you
doing?

07:24.226 --> 07:25.619
- How the fuck you think I'm
doing, man?

07:25.662 --> 07:27.621
Waiting out here in West
Bumblefuck for your ass, man.

07:27.664 --> 07:28.752
What's up?

07:28.796 --> 07:29.797
- Let's not waste time. You got
the money?

07:29.840 --> 07:31.581
- Yo, I aint wasting the time,
man.

07:33.104 --> 07:35.367
All right, yeah, I got your
paper. You got my shit?

07:35.411 --> 07:36.238
Si.

07:37.195 --> 07:39.502
All right. What's up, Jose?

07:40.677 --> 07:42.592
Oh, you too hard for that shit,
right?

07:42.636 --> 07:45.073
[scoffs] This motherfucker.

07:45.116 --> 07:46.378
So what's up, man?

07:46.422 --> 07:48.076
We gonna transact, or
we gonna bullshit, what?

07:50.905 --> 07:51.688
Go check it out.

07:53.037 --> 07:54.952
- My brother's gonna get
the money from your car.

07:56.693 --> 07:59.522
- Hey, hey, hey. Yo, Rambo,
man, is that shit necessary?

07:59.566 --> 08:03.178
I'm afraid it is, amigo.

08:03.221 --> 08:05.136
- Hey, yo, what's up with
Senor Gun Show over here?

08:06.398 --> 08:08.183
- It's cool, man, just show him
the paper.

08:10.838 --> 08:12.143
Come on now, Handsome.

08:12.187 --> 08:13.928
Let me show you something real
pretty.

08:13.971 --> 08:16.408
[Jose speaking Spanish]

08:16.452 --> 08:18.062
- What's up, man? Where's my
shit?

08:20.456 --> 08:22.066
- Step into my office, my
friend.

08:23.154 --> 08:27.332
[soft suspenseful music]

08:27.376 --> 08:29.247
- About to make your day, man.
Come on.

08:30.553 --> 08:33.513
[soft suspenseful music]

08:33.556 --> 08:36.864
[Jose speaking Spanish]

08:39.301 --> 08:40.128
We happy?

08:41.172 --> 08:43.434
Yeah, that's your happy face.

08:43.479 --> 08:46.395
- Meat and potatoes, as
promised.

08:46.438 --> 08:50.225
[soft suspenseful music]

08:50.268 --> 08:52.053
Same quality as before?

08:52.096 --> 08:52.923
Even better.

08:54.490 --> 08:57.145
[plastic snapping]

08:59.451 --> 09:03.107
- Yeah. We're good, give him the
money.

09:03.151 --> 09:04.544
Great.

09:04.587 --> 09:07.242
Well, it's been a pleasure
doing business with you

09:07.285 --> 09:09.374
but don't take this the
wrong way when I say,

09:09.418 --> 09:11.028
I'm not gonna lose any
sleep if I never have to see

09:11.072 --> 09:12.769
your ugly fucking face ever
again.

09:14.641 --> 09:17.165
[Jose speaking Spanish]

09:17.208 --> 09:18.470
Well, that's not good.

09:18.514 --> 09:21.561
Yo, Phil. We good?

09:21.604 --> 09:22.431
Talk to me.

09:22.474 --> 09:23.954
Never better.

09:23.998 --> 09:26.740
Just think we got a little
lost in translation over here.

09:27.610 --> 09:30.178
- I'm gonna need you to pick up
that bag.

09:30.221 --> 09:34.182
Or I will end you right here,
right now.

09:34.225 --> 09:36.401
- Wait, so this whole time
you could speak English?

09:36.445 --> 09:37.577
Pick up that bag.

09:37.620 --> 09:38.186
All right.

09:39.404 --> 09:40.754
Slowly

09:40.797 --> 09:44.322
- Listen, man, okay,
it was real rude of me,

09:44.366 --> 09:46.455
and if I'm being honest with
myself,

09:46.498 --> 09:49.197
rather racist to assume
you don't speak English.

09:49.240 --> 09:50.720
[gun firing rapidly]

09:50.764 --> 09:53.549
- Hey, LAPD, motherfucker.
Drop it, drop it.

09:53.593 --> 09:54.419
Phil, talk to me.

09:55.551 --> 09:57.335
[blows striking]

09:57.379 --> 09:59.947
[both groaning]

09:59.990 --> 10:02.471
[dramatic music]

10:04.429 --> 10:06.344
He's a dead man. You both are.

10:06.388 --> 10:07.911
Shut the fuck up.

10:07.955 --> 10:08.738
Hey, Phil?

10:11.349 --> 10:12.350
[knee thudding]

10:12.394 --> 10:14.222
[both groaning]

10:14.265 --> 10:17.834
- Wait, wait! You're under
arrest, LAPD!

10:17.878 --> 10:18.922
[Phil groaning]

10:18.966 --> 10:20.315
Phil!

10:20.358 --> 10:21.838
- You might as well shoot,
because I promise you,

10:21.882 --> 10:24.580
my family will come after you
and everyone who loves you.

10:24.624 --> 10:25.625
Phil?

10:25.668 --> 10:26.930
- Till all of your lifeless
bodies

10:26.974 --> 10:28.279
are hanging from an overpass.

10:28.323 --> 10:30.499
- Hey, hey. Shut the fuck
up was not a request.

10:30.542 --> 10:33.154
Shut up. Phil!

10:33.197 --> 10:34.721
- You have the right to remain
silent.

10:34.764 --> 10:36.200
Anything you say can be used
against you in a court of law.

10:36.461 --> 10:37.506
[blows striking]

10:37.549 --> 10:38.899
[both groaning]

10:40.509 --> 10:42.119
[kick striking]

10:42.163 --> 10:43.555
You okay?

10:43.599 --> 10:46.036
[blows striking]

10:46.080 --> 10:47.385
[dramatic music]

10:47.429 --> 10:49.518
- If you can't afford an
attorney

10:49.561 --> 10:51.476
one will be appointed for you.

10:51.520 --> 10:54.218
[kick striking]

10:54.262 --> 10:56.743
Have you understood these rights
as I have read them to you?

10:56.786 --> 11:00.050
Hey, amigo. Buddy?

11:00.094 --> 11:01.443
Ah, shit.

11:01.486 --> 11:04.228
Hey, Mark, do you think
he heard that last part

11:04.272 --> 11:06.535
or am I gonna have to read
him his whole Miranda rights

11:06.578 --> 11:09.799
warning all over again,
because I don't wanna.

11:09.843 --> 11:11.105
- Well, judging by his rap
sheet,

11:11.148 --> 11:12.584
I think he's heard it before.

11:12.628 --> 11:15.326
You, uh, look clean.

11:15.370 --> 11:17.241
Your guy, he was a lot smaller.

11:18.547 --> 11:21.245
- True. Maybe you should cuff
him.

11:21.289 --> 11:22.377
I don't know if you
have the punching power

11:22.420 --> 11:24.553
to keep him out very long.

11:24.596 --> 11:26.468
- Oh, he's got jokes,
and white pants. Heh.

11:28.383 --> 11:29.906
Hey, it is not a good time.

11:30.690 --> 11:34.084
[soft mournful music]

12:12.209 --> 12:15.343
We are gathered here today

12:15.386 --> 12:17.301
to celebrate the life
of our brother Akheem.

12:20.565 --> 12:22.698
I have known Akheem's mother,
Yvonne,

12:22.742 --> 12:24.352
and his brother Mark for a long
time.

12:26.789 --> 12:29.009
I can remember the day Akheem
was born,

12:30.575 --> 12:34.492
bringing with him into this
world, and to this island,

12:34.536 --> 12:36.451
that infectious smile that all
of us

12:36.494 --> 12:38.453
would soon know and love.

12:39.584 --> 12:43.501
I ask all of you now to
remember fondly Akheem

12:43.545 --> 12:45.112
and his infectious smile.

12:46.635 --> 12:50.682
But also to let his
tragic death be a reminder

12:50.726 --> 12:53.511
that we must collectively
guard the lives of our youths.

12:55.687 --> 12:57.167
Because make no mistake about
it,

12:59.039 --> 13:02.607
whereas our island is
surely a gift from God,

13:02.651 --> 13:06.002
lest we forget the devil does
not strike at us from afar.

13:07.482 --> 13:11.703
No. He slithers along
the soil we call home.

13:12.792 --> 13:14.619
Waiting to coil around the feet

13:14.663 --> 13:16.665
of any who dare oppose him.

13:16.708 --> 13:20.103
[soft mournful music]

13:35.162 --> 13:38.034
Yvonne, I am so sorry.

13:40.689 --> 13:42.560
Thank you, Akilah.

13:42.604 --> 13:45.825
[soft piano music]

13:45.868 --> 13:49.045
Please, come see me soon.

13:50.873 --> 13:53.528
[Yvonne crying]

13:56.183 --> 13:58.663
- We never met. I'm Manuel
Alvarez.

13:58.707 --> 14:02.624
I'm terribly sorry. My deepest
condolence.

14:02.667 --> 14:06.584
[soft piano music]

14:06.628 --> 14:09.239
If there is anything I can do
for you, please let me know.

14:13.983 --> 14:16.203
I'm so sorry for your loss.

14:16.246 --> 14:19.119
[soft mournful music]

14:31.653 --> 14:33.568
[door closing]

14:33.611 --> 14:36.527
[soft mournful music]

14:38.703 --> 14:41.706
- I'm sorry, Son. I didn't get
a chance to clean the house.

14:41.750 --> 14:43.012
Mom, it's fine, it's fine.

14:43.056 --> 14:44.144
- But I'm glad you're home,
baby.

14:44.187 --> 14:45.623
Me too.

14:45.667 --> 14:47.974
- Let me get you something
to eat. You must be hungry.

14:48.017 --> 14:50.150
- No, Mom. Mom, Mom, please,
please stop.

14:50.193 --> 14:51.673
I just want you to relax.

14:51.716 --> 14:54.502
You don't need to be doing
anything right now. Come, sit.

14:54.545 --> 14:55.329
Come, sit.

14:56.504 --> 14:59.333
- I have some things from your
brother.

14:59.376 --> 15:00.247
Okay.

15:00.290 --> 15:02.423
[soft music]

15:23.966 --> 15:25.925
He was wearing that when ...

15:27.709 --> 15:29.450
I'd like you to have it.

15:29.493 --> 15:31.669
[soft music]

15:35.499 --> 15:36.631
Thanks, Mom.

15:36.674 --> 15:39.025
[soft music]

15:42.724 --> 15:43.725
Tell me what happened.

15:44.769 --> 15:46.641
I don't, I don't know.

15:46.684 --> 15:49.905
He got a job, and he was
staying out of trouble.

15:49.949 --> 15:51.863
Trouble?

15:51.907 --> 15:54.692
- A lot has changed over
the past seven years

15:54.736 --> 15:56.303
since you've been gone, Son.

15:56.346 --> 15:59.567
The island just isn't the same
anymore.

15:59.610 --> 16:00.829
- I'm gonna find out what
happened.

16:00.872 --> 16:04.789
- No, no, Mark. I just
lost one of my sons.

16:04.833 --> 16:06.704
I cannot lose another.

16:06.748 --> 16:09.142
Mom, listen to me, okay?

16:11.144 --> 16:14.799
Everything is gonna be
okay. Just trust me.

16:14.843 --> 16:16.018
Get some rest, okay?

16:17.628 --> 16:19.804
[Yvonne sobbing]

16:19.848 --> 16:22.764
[soft music]

16:22.807 --> 16:24.461
It's gonna be okay.

16:24.505 --> 16:27.638
[Yvonne crying]

16:27.682 --> 16:30.032
Hey, Mom, it's gonna be all
right.

16:30.076 --> 16:33.035
[Yvonne crying]

16:33.079 --> 16:34.558
Get some rest.

16:34.602 --> 16:36.865
Okay [cries].

16:36.908 --> 16:39.302
[soft music]

17:29.526 --> 17:32.007
[dramatic music]

17:52.593 --> 17:54.812
[gate squeaking]

17:54.856 --> 17:57.250
[soft music]

17:59.991 --> 18:01.515
- I swear to God, it's not our
stuff.

18:01.558 --> 18:02.907
I'm telling you, tell him.

18:02.951 --> 18:04.692
- Yo, somebody put that
in our car. I promise you.

18:04.735 --> 18:06.085
- We've been set up. We were set
up.

18:06.128 --> 18:07.825
A complete misunderstanding.

18:07.869 --> 18:09.784
It's a big misunderstanding,
okay?

18:09.827 --> 18:10.785
It's the truth, I swear.

18:12.743 --> 18:14.832
[knocking on door]

18:14.876 --> 18:16.791
[Nate chuckling]

18:16.834 --> 18:18.097
Yes, Brother.

18:20.577 --> 18:21.404
Long time.

18:21.448 --> 18:22.666
Yeah. Sit down, sit down.

18:28.498 --> 18:29.847
I'm really sorry about Akheem.

18:31.806 --> 18:33.416
He was a good kid.

18:33.460 --> 18:34.243
Thank you.

18:35.984 --> 18:37.159
So what have you found out?

18:41.946 --> 18:45.428
- We go way back, so I'm just
gonna give it to you straight.

18:45.472 --> 18:48.475
We don't have the same
manpower that you do in LA.

18:48.518 --> 18:49.737
I remember.

18:49.780 --> 18:50.607
So this,

18:53.175 --> 18:54.611
this is gonna take some time.

18:57.179 --> 18:59.573
And right now, we don't have
a whole lot to go off of.

19:06.928 --> 19:08.973
This is all you have?

19:10.888 --> 19:12.325
- That's everything from the
table.

19:13.587 --> 19:15.023
Maybe a fight with the gangs.

19:15.066 --> 19:15.893
Gangs?

19:18.069 --> 19:20.855
- Yeah, there's been a lotta
crime

19:20.898 --> 19:22.900
here on the island since you
been gone.

19:22.944 --> 19:24.772
Especially with gangs
from neighboring islands

19:24.815 --> 19:25.903
coming here to party.

19:25.947 --> 19:27.818
The drug traffic is way up.

19:29.211 --> 19:31.953
- So you think this is
gang-related?

19:34.912 --> 19:35.739
Like I say,

19:37.306 --> 19:39.656
this is gonna take some time to
find out

19:39.700 --> 19:42.093
what actually happened.

19:42.137 --> 19:45.401
But when I do, you'll
be the first to know.

19:46.924 --> 19:48.012
All right.

19:48.056 --> 19:51.190
[soft dramatic music]

19:53.931 --> 19:56.195
[hands smacking]

19:56.238 --> 19:59.372
[soft dramatic music]

20:07.641 --> 20:08.424
[students shouting]

20:08.468 --> 20:09.251
Nine.

20:09.295 --> 20:09.904
[students shouting]

20:09.947 --> 20:10.774
10!

20:11.210 --> 20:11.993
One!

20:12.036 --> 20:12.559
[students shouting]

20:12.602 --> 20:13.429
Two!

20:14.213 --> 20:15.039
Three!

20:15.736 --> 20:16.563
- Four!
[students shouting]

20:17.041 --> 20:17.738
- Five!
[students shouting]

20:18.042 --> 20:18.956
- Six!
[students shouting]

20:19.696 --> 20:20.871
- Seven!
[students shouting]

20:20.915 --> 20:22.046
- Eight!
[students shouting]

20:22.090 --> 20:23.222
- Nine!
[students shouting]

20:23.700 --> 20:24.658
10!

20:24.701 --> 20:25.572
[students shouting]

20:27.835 --> 20:28.662
And one!

20:28.705 --> 20:29.271
[students shouting]

20:29.315 --> 20:30.098
Two!

20:30.707 --> 20:31.273
- Three!
[students shouting]

20:31.882 --> 20:32.753
- Four!
[students shouting]

20:33.014 --> 20:34.537
Bye, Sensei Akilah.

20:34.798 --> 20:36.800
Bye, Sensei.

20:36.844 --> 20:37.801
See you guys next week.

20:42.197 --> 20:44.199
So, how's the big city treating
you?

20:45.287 --> 20:47.942
- Well, not a day goes
by that I don't think

20:47.985 --> 20:51.772
about the island, if
that's what you're asking.

20:52.947 --> 20:54.035
But you left.

20:54.992 --> 20:56.080
And you know why I left?

20:57.995 --> 20:58.822
Yeah.

21:01.042 --> 21:02.957
So, um ...

21:04.393 --> 21:06.743
Did you ever remarry?

21:07.309 --> 21:09.703
[soft music]

21:12.271 --> 21:13.097
No.

21:15.274 --> 21:16.100
You?

21:18.712 --> 21:19.539
No.

21:21.280 --> 21:24.021
[soft piano music]

21:24.065 --> 21:26.676
- Well I'm happy you kept
up with your training.

21:28.156 --> 21:30.289
How long have you had the dojo?

21:30.332 --> 21:32.378
- Ah, going on about three years
now.

21:32.421 --> 21:33.248
- Uh-huh.

21:35.903 --> 21:36.860
I'm impressed.

21:38.079 --> 21:40.386
The kids are lucky to have you.

21:40.429 --> 21:42.388
[soft piano music]

21:43.954 --> 21:45.086
You know, I um,

21:47.175 --> 21:49.133
I always hoped I'd see you
again,

21:51.484 --> 21:52.702
but not like this.

21:54.965 --> 21:56.837
I am so sorry about Akheem,
Mark.

21:59.143 --> 22:00.014
Thank you.

22:01.842 --> 22:03.104
How long are you staying for?

22:04.497 --> 22:06.934
- Long enough to find out
what happened to Akheem.

22:08.239 --> 22:10.459
I went to the police
station to talk to Nate.

22:11.373 --> 22:14.245
He says there are gangs
here on the island.

22:14.289 --> 22:16.378
Unfortunately, yeah.

22:16.422 --> 22:18.815
The gangs come over on the
weekends from other islands

22:18.859 --> 22:21.209
and bring with them more drugs
and crime.

22:21.252 --> 22:23.994
But I wouldn't hold on to too
much hope

22:24.038 --> 22:26.127
in whatever Nate says or does.

22:26.170 --> 22:27.084
Why is that?

22:29.086 --> 22:31.741
- Because people around here
are afraid to make waves.

22:32.742 --> 22:33.569
I'm listening.

22:35.571 --> 22:39.183
- This guy, Manuel
Alvarez, everyone calls him

22:39.227 --> 22:40.881
the Company because he owns
everything

22:40.924 --> 22:43.057
that's important on the island.

22:43.100 --> 22:47.017
He owns the bank, construction
companies, hotels.

22:48.367 --> 22:51.848
In less than four years, he
basically managed to control

22:51.892 --> 22:54.503
the entire economy of the
island.

22:54.547 --> 22:57.114
Not to mention the only
places that the gangs seem

22:57.158 --> 23:00.161
to avoid are the businesses he
owns.

23:00.204 --> 23:01.467
And I'm pretty sure he controls
them too,

23:01.510 --> 23:04.948
just to scare the people on the
island.

23:04.992 --> 23:07.298
So whether they like it
or not, a lot of people

23:07.342 --> 23:09.518
around here rely on him to
survive.

23:10.998 --> 23:12.521
Do you remember Vanessa?

23:13.957 --> 23:15.437
Yeah.

23:15.481 --> 23:17.613
- She's working at the bank
and told me in confidence

23:17.657 --> 23:20.050
that hundreds of millions
go through the bank now.

23:21.574 --> 23:23.967
- But what does that
have to do with Akheem?

23:26.317 --> 23:29.277
- Two months ago, Akheem took a
job

23:29.320 --> 23:32.149
as a bartender working for
Alvarez.

23:33.281 --> 23:34.108
What club?

23:35.109 --> 23:37.024
Luna. Club Luna.

23:39.940 --> 23:41.855
What are you going to do, Mark?

23:43.596 --> 23:45.206
- I'm gonna do whatever it
takes.

23:47.208 --> 23:50.124
Starting with a visit to this
Alvarez.

23:52.126 --> 23:53.083
Just be careful.

23:54.215 --> 23:56.173
[dramatic music]

24:05.444 --> 24:08.882
[engine humming]

24:08.925 --> 24:12.059
[soft dramatic music]

24:27.117 --> 24:28.467
Can I help you?

24:28.510 --> 24:30.599
Here to speak to your boss.

24:30.643 --> 24:32.906
- You're gonna have to
make an appointment.

24:32.949 --> 24:34.473
Not my style.

24:34.516 --> 24:37.040
- Your style? Perhaps you've not
heard--

24:37.084 --> 24:37.911
It's okay.

24:39.826 --> 24:40.609
Please.

24:42.002 --> 24:42.829
Come, sit down.

24:44.439 --> 24:45.005
No thank you.

24:47.268 --> 24:49.400
- Can I get you something to
drink?

24:49.444 --> 24:50.010
No.

24:52.012 --> 24:54.101
So, how can I help you?

24:56.103 --> 24:58.061
My brother worked for you?

24:58.105 --> 25:00.673
- He did. A lot of people work
for me.

25:02.065 --> 25:03.327
Mm. Here at this bar?

25:03.371 --> 25:06.417
- Yes. And he was a good
bartender.

25:06.461 --> 25:07.810
- So you're aware that
my brother was killed

25:07.854 --> 25:09.551
the night he was working here?

25:09.595 --> 25:12.249
You know, I don't think I like

25:12.293 --> 25:13.947
the implication you are making.

25:15.122 --> 25:16.863
- I look like I care what you
think?

25:18.473 --> 25:20.040
What the fuck happened to my
brother?

25:24.087 --> 25:25.785
You are upset, and I get it.

25:27.221 --> 25:28.527
And I'm here to help,

25:28.570 --> 25:30.659
but you're not going to find the
answer

25:30.703 --> 25:32.618
you're looking for here.

25:32.661 --> 25:36.404
Your brother left after
his shift at night,

25:36.447 --> 25:38.667
and it seems to me he
may have gotten himself

25:38.711 --> 25:41.061
into some troubles with the
gangs.

25:41.104 --> 25:45.021
[soft dramatic music]

25:45.065 --> 25:48.459
[pen scribbling]

25:48.503 --> 25:49.069
Here.

25:51.550 --> 25:52.159
What is this?

25:53.900 --> 25:56.163
A spot, a bar actually,

25:56.206 --> 25:58.208
where a lot of the gangs

25:58.252 --> 26:00.297
that come over from
other islands hang out.

26:01.472 --> 26:02.822
My people have told me that your
brother

26:02.865 --> 26:04.693
used to go there after work.

26:06.608 --> 26:09.872
This is not the same island
you grew up on. Not anymore.

26:11.308 --> 26:13.006
- You know, everybody
keeps telling me that.

26:14.442 --> 26:18.446
- Change is inevitable.
Good and bad, I'm afraid.

26:18.489 --> 26:21.144
- You're right about
that. Changes are coming.

26:22.537 --> 26:26.019
So you might wanna move your
business off of the island.

26:26.062 --> 26:26.628
Oh [chuckles].

26:28.587 --> 26:31.241
A threat by an LA police
officer?

26:32.460 --> 26:36.290
Yes, I have friends all over
America.

26:37.465 --> 26:39.902
I did my homework on you, Mark.

26:41.251 --> 26:43.253
Apparently not enough.

26:43.297 --> 26:44.951
Otherwise, you'd be packing
right now.

26:46.300 --> 26:49.477
I've done my homework
on you too, Mr. Alvarez.

26:51.174 --> 26:53.829
And I know your type. And I
promise you.

26:55.265 --> 26:56.876
The weather's about to
get very bad for you here.

26:56.919 --> 27:00.053
[soft dramatic music]

27:07.103 --> 27:08.365
[ice rattling]

27:08.409 --> 27:09.802
What do you want me to do?

27:13.719 --> 27:15.242
[Manuel sighing]

27:16.809 --> 27:20.247
- Get the gangs from
the north to handle him.

27:20.290 --> 27:23.206
[soft dramatic music]

27:26.688 --> 27:29.125
[engine humming]

27:32.389 --> 27:35.088
[food sizzling]

27:42.399 --> 27:43.226
Teseam?

27:44.445 --> 27:47.491
Mark. My brother.

27:47.535 --> 27:49.102
Welcome home and good to see
you.

27:49.145 --> 27:50.277
You hungry? Hey, let me hook you
up, man.

27:50.320 --> 27:51.539
Nah nah, nah nah.

27:51.582 --> 27:55.021
No thanks, man. I'm
here for something else.

27:56.936 --> 27:58.981
Man, I'm sorry about Akheem.

27:59.721 --> 28:01.244
I really wanted to go to the
funeral,

28:01.288 --> 28:03.812
but with six mouths to
feed now, I got to--

28:03.856 --> 28:06.336
- Wait. You and Dayana
got four more kids now?

28:06.380 --> 28:08.121
- Yeah, brother, we've been
blessed.

28:09.470 --> 28:12.125
But things have been tough,

28:12.168 --> 28:13.604
at least for those of us who
still choose

28:13.648 --> 28:15.606
to do things the right way, you
know?

28:17.565 --> 28:18.392
Yeah.

28:20.437 --> 28:23.310
You remember that package
I asked you to hold for me?

28:23.353 --> 28:26.574
- Of course. I buried
it where you told me to.

28:26.617 --> 28:28.532
Good. I'm gonna need it.

28:30.491 --> 28:31.448
Shit is coming.

28:31.492 --> 28:33.537
- Shit is coming big time,
brother.

28:33.581 --> 28:35.452
[dramatic music]

28:44.766 --> 28:46.507
[hammer striking]

28:48.074 --> 28:49.249
[hammer striking]

28:52.382 --> 28:54.297
[hammer striking]

28:54.341 --> 28:56.169
[dramatic music]

29:01.435 --> 29:04.003
[latch opening]

29:04.046 --> 29:06.440
[dramatic music]

29:06.483 --> 29:09.617
[upbeat music]

29:09.660 --> 29:12.489
[indistinct singing]

29:14.796 --> 29:19.670
♪ Only to be trapped in a
nightmare world of madness ♪

29:19.714 --> 29:22.021
[upbeat music]

29:24.197 --> 29:27.243
[indistinct singing]

29:29.202 --> 29:30.638
♪ Only to be ♪

29:31.770 --> 29:34.163
Hey, man, what the fuck?

29:34.642 --> 29:36.470
Which of you is in charge?

29:36.513 --> 29:38.472
- Yo, big man, might wanna get
outta here

29:38.515 --> 29:40.256
before you get hurt, yeah?

29:40.300 --> 29:43.303
- Look, I don't want any
trouble.

29:43.346 --> 29:45.392
- Yo, bitch, if you're a
cop, we got nothing to say.

29:46.654 --> 29:48.221
[fingers snapping]

29:51.572 --> 29:55.010
- Like I said, all I
want is some information.

29:55.794 --> 29:57.317
My brother--

29:57.360 --> 29:58.535
- If you're not a cop, you're
in the wrong fucking place.

29:59.667 --> 30:00.624
I'm not here as a cop.

30:01.930 --> 30:03.714
I'm here as a brother of the
island

30:03.758 --> 30:05.368
who has lost his brother.

30:05.847 --> 30:08.676
And all I want is a little
information

30:08.719 --> 30:10.852
about what happened to my
brother.

30:10.896 --> 30:13.899
- Motherfucker, you do see
I got a loaded gun, right?

30:13.942 --> 30:16.858
- Look, I realize you guys
are not from the island,

30:16.902 --> 30:19.643
so you don't know me or my
reputation.

30:19.687 --> 30:20.731
Shoot this motherfucker, man.

30:20.775 --> 30:22.342
All I want is ...

30:25.519 --> 30:26.694
some information.

30:30.132 --> 30:34.136
Like I said, I'm not here to
hurt anyone.

30:34.180 --> 30:34.745
Okay?

30:38.619 --> 30:42.710
All I wanna know is if my
brother Akheem was here

30:42.753 --> 30:44.668
on the night that he was
murdered.

30:44.712 --> 30:45.800
[attacker groaning]

30:45.844 --> 30:48.585
[blows striking]

30:51.327 --> 30:53.242
[gun firing]

30:53.286 --> 30:54.765
[kick striking]

30:54.809 --> 30:57.246
[intense dramatic music]

30:59.640 --> 31:01.555
[blows striking]

31:01.598 --> 31:04.210
[both groaning]

31:06.255 --> 31:07.648
[attacker screaming]

31:09.519 --> 31:11.217
[Mark groaning]

31:12.348 --> 31:14.263
[blows striking]

31:14.307 --> 31:16.004
[attacker groaning]

31:18.789 --> 31:20.226
[bones cracking]

31:28.625 --> 31:30.540
[blows striking]

31:30.584 --> 31:32.760
[head banging]

31:32.803 --> 31:35.806
[attacker groaning]

31:36.720 --> 31:38.679
[body crashing]

31:42.378 --> 31:45.991
- You broke my fucking nose
[spits].

31:46.034 --> 31:47.557
- You wanna tell me about my
brother now?

31:47.601 --> 31:48.907
Fuck your brother.

31:48.950 --> 31:50.473
[blows striking]

31:50.517 --> 31:52.258
[attacker groaning]

31:52.301 --> 31:53.824
[kicks striking]

31:59.700 --> 32:01.310
[body thudding]

32:05.532 --> 32:07.621
- That's right. Had it, didn't
need it.

32:09.710 --> 32:11.190
I could use it now if you like.

32:13.583 --> 32:16.195
- I don't know him. I never met
him.

32:16.238 --> 32:17.848
We were just told to fuck some
dude up

32:17.892 --> 32:18.806
looking for his brother.

32:19.894 --> 32:21.809
That's all I know. I swear.

32:21.852 --> 32:24.464
I believe you. Thank you.

32:24.507 --> 32:26.509
[kick striking]

32:26.553 --> 32:28.468
[engine roaring]

32:29.773 --> 32:30.513
Yo, that's him!

32:30.557 --> 32:33.038
[guns firing]

32:35.388 --> 32:36.389
He's here!

32:36.432 --> 32:38.652
[guns firing]

32:43.744 --> 32:44.832
Let's go!

32:44.875 --> 32:47.835
[engines roaring]

32:47.878 --> 32:49.924
[dramatic music]

32:53.754 --> 32:55.408
[engines revving]

32:55.451 --> 32:57.801
[brake squealing]

32:57.845 --> 33:01.196
[intense dramatic music]

33:02.545 --> 33:03.590
That way!

33:03.633 --> 33:05.505
[engines roaring]

33:10.684 --> 33:13.513
[guns firing]

33:13.556 --> 33:16.646
[engines revving]

33:16.690 --> 33:19.867
[intense dramatic music]

33:28.006 --> 33:28.658
Shoot him.

33:28.702 --> 33:30.008
[guns firing]

33:31.618 --> 33:33.141
[intense dramatic music]

33:42.890 --> 33:44.848
[soft suspenseful music]

33:47.503 --> 33:49.853
Yo, you guys see him anywhere?

33:49.897 --> 33:51.377
Shit, we lost him.

33:53.074 --> 33:53.857
Let's go.

33:53.901 --> 33:55.990
[engines roaring]

33:56.860 --> 33:58.775
[soft suspenseful music]

34:08.524 --> 34:09.395
Fuck. I'll call him.

34:11.571 --> 34:13.485
We lost him.

34:13.529 --> 34:15.835
- [Manuel] That's very
disappointing.

34:15.879 --> 34:18.230
I will deal with your failures
later.

34:18.273 --> 34:21.929
Go to the mother's house.
Use her to flush him out.

34:21.972 --> 34:23.061
Understood.

34:23.800 --> 34:25.411
[phone beeping]

34:25.454 --> 34:27.195
[engines roaring]

34:53.873 --> 34:55.963
[door opening]

34:56.703 --> 34:58.922
[soft suspenseful music]

35:21.989 --> 35:22.772
Going dark.

35:22.816 --> 35:25.427
[dramatic music]

35:58.678 --> 36:01.289
[guns firing rapidly]

36:07.600 --> 36:08.644
Fuck!

36:08.688 --> 36:10.951
[suspenseful music]

36:40.763 --> 36:42.200
Here you go.

36:42.243 --> 36:43.679
Thank you.

36:43.723 --> 36:44.506
Don't mention it.

36:48.249 --> 36:51.383
Yvonne, everything is going to
be okay.

36:52.253 --> 36:54.777
He's going to be okay.

36:54.821 --> 36:58.607
- You know, when you're a
mother, you always have to worry.

36:58.651 --> 37:01.306
[soft piano music]

37:02.916 --> 37:05.962
I'm sorry. I wasn't thinking.

37:06.006 --> 37:07.094
I'm so sorry.

37:07.137 --> 37:08.095
It's okay.

37:10.358 --> 37:12.926
You know I really wish
that I could tell you

37:12.969 --> 37:15.145
that after losing a child it
gets easier.

37:16.843 --> 37:18.671
But even after seven years,

37:20.716 --> 37:21.587
it doesn't.

37:25.634 --> 37:27.984
[door opening]

37:28.028 --> 37:30.335
[soft piano music]

37:30.378 --> 37:32.032
You two good?

37:32.075 --> 37:33.251
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

37:34.948 --> 37:36.297
- You have a first-aid kit?

37:36.341 --> 37:38.212
Yeah, I'll go grab it.

37:38.256 --> 37:39.344
All right.

37:39.387 --> 37:42.869
[police radio chattering]

37:45.915 --> 37:47.830
All right, so what we got?

37:47.874 --> 37:50.659
- We have a DOA. The rest
have gone on to the hospital.

37:52.966 --> 37:55.838
- Jesus Christ. These boys got
hit hard.

37:57.405 --> 37:58.319
Who else see it?

37:58.363 --> 37:59.059
No one's talking.

38:00.321 --> 38:02.802
[Nate sighing]

38:02.845 --> 38:04.238
- All right, I'll take it from
here.

38:04.282 --> 38:05.674
Just make sure you secure the
perimeter.

38:05.718 --> 38:06.501
Yes, sir.

38:08.068 --> 38:08.895
Excuse me, sir.

38:08.938 --> 38:10.288
Yes, Officer.

38:10.331 --> 38:11.637
- The station has been
trying to get hold of you.

38:11.680 --> 38:12.855
What is it?

38:12.899 --> 38:13.943
- They say there's a possible
crime scene

38:13.987 --> 38:15.423
that you'd want to know about.

38:16.772 --> 38:18.339
- I have a crime scene here
already.

38:18.383 --> 38:20.950
- It's at Akheem's mother's
house.

38:20.994 --> 38:23.039
[soft dramatic music]

38:23.910 --> 38:25.128
Tell them I'm on my way.

38:25.172 --> 38:26.347
Okay, sir.

38:26.391 --> 38:28.262
[soft dramatic music]

38:35.138 --> 38:37.010
[knocking on door]

38:42.189 --> 38:44.800
Good thing nobody was home.

38:44.844 --> 38:45.845
This time.

38:49.370 --> 38:51.067
- Any idea what happened
to a buncha gang members

38:51.111 --> 38:52.939
earlier tonight at the beach
bar?

38:52.982 --> 38:54.897
Hm?

38:55.376 --> 38:57.204
- Any idea what happened
to my brother or who tried

38:57.247 --> 38:59.075
to break into my mother's
house and kill her?

39:00.250 --> 39:03.950
- You have no idea what you
are asking of me right now.

39:05.821 --> 39:08.694
This? This is so much
bigger than your brother.

39:09.999 --> 39:13.176
- You're right. It's not gonna
stop.

39:13.220 --> 39:15.135
Not unless you help me to make
it stop.

39:17.093 --> 39:17.964
- I think you already know the
answers

39:18.007 --> 39:19.792
to the questions you're asking.

39:19.835 --> 39:22.490
This is our island, our home.

39:24.536 --> 39:27.974
My father build this
house with his bare hands

39:28.017 --> 39:29.584
just like your father built
yours.

39:30.933 --> 39:33.240
They wanted my mother to be
there, Nate.

39:34.415 --> 39:35.547
Changes are coming.

39:37.462 --> 39:39.855
And you need to decide
what side of those changes

39:39.899 --> 39:41.379
you're gonna be standing on.

39:41.422 --> 39:44.556
[soft dramatic music]

39:53.347 --> 39:54.914
- Speak to the Luna's new
singer.

39:56.306 --> 39:58.047
One of my informants
told me she was working

39:58.091 --> 39:59.832
the night your brother was
killed.

40:00.920 --> 40:02.356
Her name's Nora.

40:02.400 --> 40:04.837
She's staying at the motel
by the church, Room 18.

40:06.099 --> 40:08.057
[soft dramatic music]

40:08.101 --> 40:09.537
Is your mother somewhere safe?

40:10.451 --> 40:11.017
Yeah.

40:13.193 --> 40:14.499
At Akilah's place.

40:15.761 --> 40:16.544
Good.

40:19.155 --> 40:20.505
I need to trust you, Nate.

40:22.158 --> 40:25.205
This island needs help,
and I can't do it alone.

40:25.640 --> 40:28.774
[soft dramatic music]

40:49.142 --> 40:52.058
[lighter clicking]

40:54.626 --> 40:58.281
- I don't think the word
disappointed carries enough weight

40:58.325 --> 41:00.109
for what I'm feeling right now.

41:00.153 --> 41:02.416
- We did what you asked, Boss,
after we lost him in town,

41:02.460 --> 41:06.507
but the house, it's empty.

41:06.551 --> 41:08.901
They must have known someone was
coming.

41:08.944 --> 41:11.469
So, this was my fault?

41:11.991 --> 41:14.210
- No, no, that's not what I
meant, no.

41:14.254 --> 41:16.865
- Sh. It's okay, forget about
it.

41:18.345 --> 41:19.825
You tried, right?

41:19.868 --> 41:22.001
You did the best you could
with the information you had,

41:22.044 --> 41:24.046
but they knew you were coming.

41:25.091 --> 41:25.918
Right?

41:26.962 --> 41:28.224
- Y-yes, sir. Y-yes, sir.

41:30.705 --> 41:32.664
Hey, hey, take it easy.

41:33.708 --> 41:36.450
Take a deep breath before
you're hyperventilating.

41:36.494 --> 41:38.104
[dramatic music]

41:38.147 --> 41:41.150
[assailant gasping]

41:47.983 --> 41:50.377
One thing I can't stand is
excuses.

41:51.552 --> 41:53.119
And a lack of accountability.

41:54.033 --> 41:56.992
[assailant gasping]

41:58.341 --> 41:59.168
Please.

42:01.431 --> 42:02.432
Please, please!

42:05.958 --> 42:06.436
So,

42:06.480 --> 42:07.525
Fuck.

42:07.568 --> 42:10.179
- let's get back
to the accountability.

42:12.312 --> 42:13.792
Please, no no no!
Wait wait wait, wait!

42:13.835 --> 42:16.142
I have a photo, in my pocket.

42:16.185 --> 42:19.275
[assailant breathing hard]

42:19.319 --> 42:22.235
[soft dramatic music]

42:26.065 --> 42:27.457
I think I know how to get this
guy.

42:27.501 --> 42:30.025
She, she's a local. Runs the
island dojo.

42:31.461 --> 42:33.594
[gun firing]

42:33.638 --> 42:35.988
[body splashing]

42:36.031 --> 42:39.165
[soft dramatic music]

42:43.909 --> 42:44.953
Are you gonna come back inside

42:44.997 --> 42:46.172
and finish fucking me or what?

42:47.956 --> 42:49.044
I'll be back in a moment.

42:50.785 --> 42:53.832
- This cop? More trouble than we
expected.

42:54.746 --> 42:57.183
He put the boys in the
north gang in the hospital.

43:01.274 --> 43:03.232
- Make a call to our
special friends, okay?

43:04.756 --> 43:06.453
[soft dramatic music]

43:16.202 --> 43:18.770
[bird calling]

43:32.522 --> 43:33.567
[Nora] Who is it?

43:33.611 --> 43:36.004
- I'm a police officer from Los
Angeles.

43:36.048 --> 43:38.441
[waves lapping]

43:40.400 --> 43:41.488
Nora, please open the door.

43:44.709 --> 43:46.319
My name is Mark Ethridge.

43:46.362 --> 43:48.277
Akheem the bartender was my
brother.

43:53.587 --> 43:57.025
Listen, if you know the
information I'm looking for,

43:57.069 --> 43:58.897
then you're not safe, not here,

43:58.940 --> 44:01.943
not anywhere on the
island, but I can help you.

44:04.554 --> 44:06.078
Are you really a cop from LA?

44:10.343 --> 44:13.259
[soft dramatic music]

44:15.609 --> 44:18.090
[lock unhooking]

44:18.133 --> 44:21.006
[soft dramatic music]

44:32.060 --> 44:33.671
- You tell me about what you
know,

44:33.714 --> 44:35.150
and I will get you off this
island.

44:37.675 --> 44:40.112
I can't. They will kill me.

44:42.375 --> 44:45.204
You have to go. If they
see me talking to you--

44:45.247 --> 44:48.860
- No no, Nora, Nora, Nora.
Please.

44:48.903 --> 44:51.384
Just, look, calm down.

44:53.299 --> 44:55.605
No one is here, and no
one is going to kill you.

44:56.737 --> 44:59.827
Now it is my job to protect
people in your situation

44:59.871 --> 45:03.091
and I swear I will get
you back to the U.S.

45:04.527 --> 45:07.530
When? When can you got me out?

45:07.574 --> 45:10.055
- If you tell me what
happened to my brother,

45:10.098 --> 45:13.841
I will get you out today, okay?

45:13.885 --> 45:16.626
I will have my partner
meet you at the airport

45:16.670 --> 45:20.195
back in the U.S., and he
will make sure you're safe.

45:20.239 --> 45:23.459
But, I need to know what
happened.

45:23.503 --> 45:26.419
[soft dramatic music]

45:29.465 --> 45:31.554
[Nora sighing]

45:34.644 --> 45:35.471
He killed him.

45:37.691 --> 45:38.953
Right in front of me.

45:40.346 --> 45:43.001
Because he spilled some wine on
me.

45:43.044 --> 45:43.653
Alvarez?

45:48.049 --> 45:48.702
Yes.

45:48.746 --> 45:52.140
[soft dramatic music]

45:54.273 --> 45:56.101
I see it every time I close my
eyes.

45:58.190 --> 45:59.234
I'm so sorry.

46:01.497 --> 46:04.849
I am so sorry [cries].

46:04.892 --> 46:08.026
[soft dramatic music]

46:09.636 --> 46:11.420
I just came here to sing
[cries].

46:16.295 --> 46:17.470
It's gonna be okay.

46:17.513 --> 46:20.647
[intense dramatic music]

46:22.649 --> 46:26.305
[engine humming]

46:26.348 --> 46:29.134
[dramatic music]

46:53.506 --> 46:55.508
[birds calling]

47:01.557 --> 47:02.428
Come on.

47:10.262 --> 47:12.307
Don't worry. You can trust him.

47:12.351 --> 47:13.613
Are you sure?

47:13.656 --> 47:16.616
- I promise you. He's
one of the good guys.

47:18.748 --> 47:21.403
Hey, I wanna thank you for
telling me

47:21.447 --> 47:23.318
about what happened to my
brother.

47:29.847 --> 47:30.848
So how we looking?

47:30.891 --> 47:31.674
We're good.

47:33.198 --> 47:35.504
- Are you sure it isn't better
for her to stick around?

47:35.548 --> 47:37.767
We could arrest him now, and
with her testimony we could--

47:37.811 --> 47:40.509
- There isn't gonna be any
trial.

47:43.643 --> 47:45.340
And I promised to get her off
the island.

47:47.560 --> 47:48.387
We better get going.

47:49.301 --> 47:50.563
Thank you.

47:50.606 --> 47:52.260
- No need to thank me
for doing what's right.

47:55.394 --> 47:56.786
You can come with me.

47:56.830 --> 47:58.005
It's all right.

47:59.267 --> 48:02.401
[soft suspenseful music]

48:13.586 --> 48:14.674
I've got news.

48:18.112 --> 48:22.377
There was an eyewitness.
Alvarez killed Akheem.

48:22.769 --> 48:24.902
[Yvonne crying]

48:24.945 --> 48:28.079
[soft mournful music]

48:35.390 --> 48:37.871
[dramatic music]

49:04.898 --> 49:07.553
[birds calling]

49:09.511 --> 49:11.992
- Everything has been taken care
of.

49:12.036 --> 49:13.472
This boat will take you to a
taxi

49:13.515 --> 49:15.387
that will get you to the
airport.

49:18.912 --> 49:20.479
You can trust him.

49:25.571 --> 49:26.224
Here's your ticket.

49:29.357 --> 49:30.706
Mark's partner, Phil,
will be waiting for you

49:30.750 --> 49:31.577
when you reach Miami.

49:33.840 --> 49:34.667
Thank you.

49:35.624 --> 49:36.451
One last thing.

49:38.976 --> 49:40.760
Leave the demons you're
carrying, the ones in your head,

49:40.803 --> 49:41.891
behind on this island.

49:43.981 --> 49:45.895
There's no reason for you
to carry them anymore.

49:47.680 --> 49:50.378
[soft piano music]

49:57.559 --> 50:00.388
[engine starting]

50:25.761 --> 50:29.156
[intense dramatic music]

50:35.597 --> 50:36.859
Here you go.

50:36.903 --> 50:38.470
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

50:38.513 --> 50:40.559
[engine revving]

50:43.127 --> 50:44.954
- We got company. We gotta move,
go.

50:45.564 --> 50:46.782
What's going on, Mark?

50:46.826 --> 50:48.480
Mom, you gotta trust me.

50:49.959 --> 50:50.699
Still know how to shoot one of
these?

50:50.743 --> 50:51.570
Absolutely.

50:51.613 --> 50:53.702
All right, good. Take Mom.

50:53.746 --> 50:55.356
Okay. Okay, come on.

50:56.662 --> 50:57.663
Right behind you.

50:57.706 --> 51:00.187
[dramatic music]

51:02.798 --> 51:05.932
[intense dramatic music]

51:51.151 --> 51:53.153
[guns firing]

51:55.634 --> 51:59.551
[intense dramatic music]

51:59.594 --> 52:02.597
[guns firing]

52:02.641 --> 52:05.774
[intense dramatic music]

52:07.124 --> 52:09.126
[gun firing]

52:20.659 --> 52:23.879
[police radio chattering]

52:25.794 --> 52:28.319
[phone vibrating]

52:30.234 --> 52:32.801
Oh, you got to be kidding me.

52:36.849 --> 52:39.112
[siren blaring]

52:39.156 --> 52:41.114
[intense dramatic music]

52:55.607 --> 52:57.826
[siren blaring]

53:01.656 --> 53:04.181
[guns firing]

53:11.231 --> 53:13.277
[gun clicking]

53:13.320 --> 53:16.541
[intense dramatic music]

53:16.584 --> 53:19.065
[guns firing]

53:27.552 --> 53:29.293
[body thudding]

53:29.336 --> 53:31.817
[guns firing]

53:35.647 --> 53:39.303
[intense dramatic music]

53:39.346 --> 53:41.870
[guns firing]

53:46.875 --> 53:48.703
[intense dramatic music]

53:48.747 --> 53:51.097
[Nate breathing hard]

53:54.318 --> 53:56.537
[guns firing]

53:58.974 --> 54:01.368
[gun firing]

54:04.806 --> 54:06.982
[tires squealing]

54:07.026 --> 54:09.420
[gun firing]

54:10.943 --> 54:11.770
Shit.

54:12.771 --> 54:13.989
- You okay?
- Yes.

54:14.033 --> 54:14.816
You good?

54:14.860 --> 54:15.730
I'm good.

54:15.991 --> 54:17.166
Mom, you okay?

54:17.210 --> 54:18.342
- Yeah, I'm a little shaken, but
I'm okay.

54:18.385 --> 54:19.168
All right.

54:19.865 --> 54:21.649
Mark! Akilah!

54:35.794 --> 54:38.884
[phone buzzing]

54:38.927 --> 54:39.841
Go, Nate.

54:40.973 --> 54:42.366
Thank God you're all right.

54:42.409 --> 54:43.192
It's clear.

54:44.368 --> 54:45.847
They're gone for now.

54:45.891 --> 54:48.023
These guys were not amateurs.

54:48.067 --> 54:51.113
- Yeah, I know. You've awakened
the devil.

54:51.157 --> 54:52.550
You have a plan?

54:52.593 --> 54:55.901
- Yeah, first thing is to
get my mom somewhere safe.

54:55.944 --> 54:57.555
You have a place in mind?

54:57.598 --> 54:58.686
I do.

54:58.730 --> 54:59.513
Good.

55:01.036 --> 55:03.125
I'm going back to the station,
see what I can find out.

55:03.909 --> 55:06.259
- All right, meet you in a few
hours.

55:06.303 --> 55:07.260
Where?

55:07.304 --> 55:08.740
The old sugar mill.

55:08.783 --> 55:10.959
All right, stay safe.

55:12.134 --> 55:12.961
Yeah.

55:15.790 --> 55:17.923
[soft suspenseful music]

55:31.980 --> 55:34.505
[door creaking]

55:35.288 --> 55:38.422
[suspenseful music]

55:38.465 --> 55:40.032
So where is she?

55:40.075 --> 55:42.208
I thought you were keeping her
locked up.

55:50.521 --> 55:52.174
Kind of hard for her to stay
strung out

55:54.089 --> 55:55.830
if she's out of junk!

55:55.874 --> 55:57.223
She never told me she was out.

55:57.266 --> 55:59.791
Oh, she never told?

56:01.793 --> 56:02.881
I'm sorry.

56:02.924 --> 56:04.926
Okay, I know I messed up. I'm
sorry.

56:04.970 --> 56:07.189
It's okay. Forget about it.

56:08.365 --> 56:10.541
When was the last time you saw
her?

56:10.584 --> 56:14.414
- Yesterday, afternoon, when
I dropped off some dope.

56:14.458 --> 56:17.243
I gave it to her, I swear.

56:17.286 --> 56:19.201
- Did she use it, in front of
you?

56:20.420 --> 56:21.900
I, I don't remember.

56:21.943 --> 56:23.989
Oh, you don't remember?

56:25.207 --> 56:26.208
Don't remember.

56:28.341 --> 56:29.908
Do you have any on you now?

56:30.996 --> 56:32.476
What?

56:32.519 --> 56:35.000
- The drugs you give her?
Do you have some on you now?

56:35.043 --> 56:36.610
- Yeah, yeah, right here. Right
here.

56:37.524 --> 56:38.090
See?

56:40.135 --> 56:42.224
Look, I'm sorry. Okay, I'm real
sorry.

56:42.268 --> 56:43.356
I'm real sorry.

56:43.400 --> 56:44.575
[blow striking]

56:44.618 --> 56:45.837
[clerk gasping]

56:45.880 --> 56:46.881
Hold him down.

56:48.317 --> 56:50.842
No, please!

56:50.885 --> 56:51.712
Open his mouth.

56:52.931 --> 56:55.542
[clerk gasping]

56:56.717 --> 56:58.806
Swallow it!

57:01.853 --> 57:04.072
Swallow it, junkie puta!

57:12.341 --> 57:15.519
Now, that's how you keep someone
doped up.

57:15.562 --> 57:18.696
[soft dramatic music]

57:23.875 --> 57:27.139
[siren blaring in distance]

57:27.182 --> 57:30.098
[soft dramatic music]

58:13.011 --> 58:16.014
[phone ringing]

58:16.057 --> 58:17.363
Hey, Nate.

58:17.406 --> 58:19.191
Everything go as planned?

58:19.234 --> 58:22.629
- Yeah, she's safe and sound.
You get the email I sent?

58:22.673 --> 58:26.415
- Yeah, looking at it now.
Thanks for helping me with this.

58:26.459 --> 58:29.157
Our resources on the island are
tight.

58:29.201 --> 58:30.115
Yeah, happy to help.

58:32.204 --> 58:34.511
You know, the fingerprints
belong to a sicario,

58:34.554 --> 58:37.078
a member of a pretty
vicious Colombian cartel.

58:38.384 --> 58:39.690
What's going on down there, man?

58:39.733 --> 58:40.560
Give it to me straight.

58:40.604 --> 58:41.605
Mark aint telling me anything,

58:41.648 --> 58:44.346
and these are not small-town
players.

58:44.390 --> 58:45.217
I know.

58:46.305 --> 58:47.132
I got to go.

58:48.568 --> 58:49.787
Thanks again.

58:49.830 --> 58:50.396
You got it.

58:52.311 --> 58:55.706
[soft suspenseful music]

59:17.336 --> 59:20.252
[printer whirring]

59:23.951 --> 59:26.519
[horn beeping]

59:26.563 --> 59:29.000
[doors closing]

59:30.567 --> 59:32.264
- Hey, Yvonne. Good to see you,
welcome.

59:32.960 --> 59:33.831
Akilah.

59:33.874 --> 59:35.267
Hi, Teseam. Glad to see you.

59:35.615 --> 59:36.442
Hey, Brother.

59:36.964 --> 59:39.358
[children laughing]

59:39.401 --> 59:40.968
Hey, guys, let's go. Come
inside.

59:41.882 --> 59:43.275
Welcome to my home.

59:47.192 --> 59:50.282
Hey, you kids be careful
around our guests, okay?

59:50.325 --> 59:52.676
- It's okay, the laughter of
children

59:52.719 --> 59:54.503
is the most beautiful thing in
the world.

59:55.766 --> 59:58.943
You know, I remember when
you two were the same age,

59:58.986 --> 01:00:00.205
nothing but trouble [laughs].

01:00:04.078 --> 01:00:05.471
Kids, get in here and eat.

01:00:07.038 --> 01:00:08.213
I'll help you with that.

01:00:08.517 --> 01:00:11.129
- Thanks, Yvonne. Welcome to our
home.

01:00:11.172 --> 01:00:11.999
Thank you.

01:00:12.043 --> 01:00:13.044
Hey, Dayana.

01:00:13.087 --> 01:00:14.480
- Hello, Mark. It's good to see
you.

01:00:14.523 --> 01:00:15.350
You too.

01:00:17.614 --> 01:00:18.702
Are you sure this is okay?

01:00:18.745 --> 01:00:20.268
Of course.

01:00:20.312 --> 01:00:21.400
Dayana and I wish that there
was more we could do to help.

01:00:21.443 --> 01:00:24.446
- Hey, taking care of my mother
and Akilah

01:00:24.490 --> 01:00:26.405
is more than enough, bro.

01:00:26.448 --> 01:00:28.625
- You mean taking care of your
mother.

01:00:28.668 --> 01:00:30.322
I'm not staying.

01:00:30.365 --> 01:00:31.497
Akilah, you need to stay here.

01:00:31.540 --> 01:00:35.109
- What I need is to be
there for my island.

01:00:35.153 --> 01:00:36.545
Akilah, please.

01:00:36.589 --> 01:00:38.069
And to be there for you too.

01:00:38.939 --> 01:00:41.072
[soft music]

01:00:44.466 --> 01:00:47.121
- All right. I'll be
back as soon as I can.

01:00:49.297 --> 01:00:50.908
Stay safe, my friends.

01:00:50.951 --> 01:00:51.996
Don't worry about your mother.

01:00:52.039 --> 01:00:54.259
She gonna be safe here with us.

01:00:54.302 --> 01:00:56.130
Akilah, take care. Be safe.

01:00:56.174 --> 01:00:57.088
Thank you.

01:01:03.485 --> 01:01:06.053
[bell tolling]

01:01:13.800 --> 01:01:17.108
[footsteps approaching]

01:01:22.156 --> 01:01:24.332
[soft music]

01:01:28.206 --> 01:01:29.598
Forgive me, Father.

01:01:29.642 --> 01:01:33.298
I can't even remember the
last time I came to church.

01:01:34.865 --> 01:01:36.649
As one of God's children,

01:01:36.693 --> 01:01:38.607
all that matters is that you are
here now.

01:01:41.393 --> 01:01:43.221
Go on. What is on your mind, my
son?

01:01:44.918 --> 01:01:46.354
- I need to ask you to
do something for me.

01:01:49.749 --> 01:01:51.359
Please keep it safe.

01:01:51.403 --> 01:01:53.187
- I don't understand. What is
it?

01:01:54.536 --> 01:01:56.408
If anything happens to me,

01:01:56.451 --> 01:01:58.018
open it and I'll trust
you'll know what to do.

01:01:59.237 --> 01:02:01.413
[soft music]

01:02:06.157 --> 01:02:09.116
[singer vocalizing]

01:02:12.598 --> 01:02:14.992
[birds singing and calling]

01:02:15.035 --> 01:02:18.125
- We could be in real trouble
here.

01:02:18.517 --> 01:02:20.301
We sent the Amore.

01:02:20.345 --> 01:02:24.479
Si, Carla [speaks Spanish].

01:02:24.523 --> 01:02:26.264
I take care, don't worry about
it, okay?

01:02:27.744 --> 01:02:29.528
I might have a solution.

01:02:29.571 --> 01:02:32.009
- You better, because if they
have her,

01:02:32.052 --> 01:02:34.185
then she can testify against
you.

01:02:34.228 --> 01:02:35.447
I'll find her.

01:02:35.490 --> 01:02:36.970
No you won't.

01:02:37.014 --> 01:02:39.016
If she's gone, it means they got
to her.

01:02:40.017 --> 01:02:42.367
And if they got to her, then
that means

01:02:42.410 --> 01:02:44.673
they can bring an international
warrant against me.

01:02:46.545 --> 01:02:48.677
And if you're still here,

01:02:48.721 --> 01:02:51.768
it means that little piece
of shit is still breathing.

01:02:51.811 --> 01:02:54.466
- He is, but we have a card to
play,

01:02:54.509 --> 01:02:55.815
if you're willing to play it.

01:02:55.859 --> 01:02:59.253
- I'm willing to play
it. Do what it takes.

01:02:59.297 --> 01:03:00.341
It's messy.

01:03:00.385 --> 01:03:01.908
- Everything I did for this
island

01:03:01.952 --> 01:03:04.476
is in jeopardy because of this
man!

01:03:04.519 --> 01:03:07.696
I will make a mess if
I have to, believe me.

01:03:07.740 --> 01:03:11.178
[soft suspenseful music]

01:03:23.669 --> 01:03:26.672
[crickets chirping]

01:03:31.285 --> 01:03:33.461
- I don't understand
why you just don't let

01:03:33.505 --> 01:03:34.854
Nate make a case against him.

01:03:34.898 --> 01:03:37.204
And put an end to all of this.

01:03:37.248 --> 01:03:39.163
With that singer's testimony,

01:03:39.206 --> 01:03:41.426
he'll spend the rest of his life
in jail.

01:03:41.469 --> 01:03:44.342
- Because guys like him
don't end up in jail, Akilah.

01:03:45.560 --> 01:03:48.389
- Mark, he's never going to
stop.

01:03:48.433 --> 01:03:49.173
And neither am I.

01:03:51.828 --> 01:03:53.220
There's only one way this ends.

01:03:56.049 --> 01:04:00.227
- To carry a life inside
of me, for nine months,

01:04:01.402 --> 01:04:03.361
one that you and I created
together.

01:04:05.711 --> 01:04:08.801
And to never get to hear her
cry.

01:04:10.716 --> 01:04:13.806
Or see her open her eyes to look
at me.

01:04:13.850 --> 01:04:16.156
To never get to hold her against
my skin.

01:04:17.375 --> 01:04:19.246
Or see her take her first steps.

01:04:20.857 --> 01:04:22.032
Or watch her grow up.

01:04:23.076 --> 01:04:23.860
Akilah.

01:04:23.903 --> 01:04:26.253
